  "prompt": "How did Stitch Fix start?",
  "response": "Stitch Fix was founded in 2011 by Katrina Lake. The idea for the company was conceived while Lake was attending Harvard Business School. She identified a gap in the market for personalized online shopping experiences and sought to combine data science with fashion to curate personalized clothing selections for customers.\n\nThe company began operations by initially sending a selection of women\u2019s clothing items and accessories to clients, based on personal style preferences collected through a detailed online questionnaire. Clients would keep and purchase what they liked and return the rest, with a styling fee applied to each order. This unique blend of personal styling, data, and convenience helped Stitch Fix rapidly grow.\n\nLake initially worked out of her apartment and personally curated the early shipments. However, the company quickly scaled up, raising venture capital and expanding its operations. By leveraging a data-driven approach to fashion, Stitch Fix was able to offer a distinctive service in the retail landscape. The company went public in 2017, with Katrina Lake being one of the few female tech founders to take a company public that year.",
